                "invention-title": [
                    "System and method for driving carbon dioxide hydrogenation by renewable energy sources",
                    "一种可再生能源驱动二氧化碳加氢的系统及方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a method for driving carbon dioxide hydrogenation by renewable energy sources, which comprises the following steps: a renewable energy source power generation device generates power by using the renewable energy sources, and the generated electric energy is stored and used by a renewable energy source storage device; carbon dioxide captured by the carbon dioxide capturing device and hydrogen obtained by the water electrolysis hydrogen production device are introduced into a raw material buffer tank, mixed and then enter a micro-reactor hydrogenation device for a carbon dioxide hydrogenation reaction; a reaction product enters a three-phase separator to be separated, and product water obtained through separation serves as an electrolyzed water raw material; the liquid product enters a liquid hydrocarbon separation system to separate out a C5 + gasoline product; the gas product enters a gas separation system to separate out unreacted carbon dioxide and hydrogen, lean dry gas, low-carbon olefin and liquefied gas; unreacted carbon dioxide and hydrogen return to the system for circulation."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种可再生能源驱动二氧化碳加氢的方法，包括如下步骤：可再生能源发电装置利用可再生能源进行发电，所产生的电能通过可再生能源储存装置进行储存并使用；将二氧化碳捕集装置捕集所得二氧化碳、电解水制氢装置所得氢气通入原料缓冲罐中，混合后进入微反应器加氢装置中进行二氧化碳加氢反应；反应产物进入三相分离器进行分离，分离得到产物水作为电解水原料；液体产物进入液体烃分离系统分离出C5+汽油产品；气体产物进入气体分离系统分离出未反应的二氧化碳和氢气、贫干气、低碳烯烃、液化气；未反应的二氧化碳和氢气回到系统中循环。"
                }
            ]
